            <title>Companies asked these questions during a job interview? Really?</title>
            <description>&lt;p&gt;
	We all know the job interview process can be stressful, but for many candidates it can feel like a pressure chamber, especially when questions seemingly come out of left field. Glassdoor.com, a career and jobs community offering insights on companies and workplaces, has compiled its annual list of oddball interview questions based on the tens of thousands of interview questions shared by job candidates during the past year.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	The Top 25 Oddball Interview Questions of 2010 on Glassdoor:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol type="1"&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
		&amp;quot;If you were shrunk to the size of a pencil and put in a blender, how would you get out?&amp;quot; &amp;ndash; Asked at &lt;a href="http://www.glassdoor.com/Interview/Goldman-Sachs-Interview-RVW515514.htm"&gt;Goldman Sachs, Analyst&lt;/a&gt; position&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
		&amp;quot;How many ridges [are there] around a quarter?&amp;quot; &amp;ndash; Asked at &lt;a href="http://www.glassdoor.com/Interview/Deloitte-Interview-RVW605296.htm"&gt;Deloitte, Project Analyst&lt;/a&gt; position&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
		&amp;quot;What is the philosophy of &lt;span class="xn-person"&gt;Martial Arts&lt;/span&gt;?&amp;quot; &amp;ndash; Asked at &lt;a href="http://www.glassdoor.com/Interview/Aflac-Interview-RVW552041.htm"&gt;Aflac, Sales Associate&lt;/a&gt; position&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
		&amp;quot;Explain [to] me what has happened in this country during the last 10 years.&amp;quot; &amp;ndash; Asked at &lt;a href="http://www.glassdoor.com/Interview/Boston-Consulting-Interview-RVW410282.htm"&gt;Boston Consulting, Consultant&lt;/a&gt; position&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
		&amp;quot;Rate yourself on a scale of 1 to 10 how weird you are.&amp;quot; &amp;ndash; Asked at &lt;a href="http://www.glassdoor.com/Interview/Capital-One-Interview-RVW453054.htm"&gt;Capital One, Operations Analyst&lt;/a&gt; position&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
		&amp;quot;How many basketball[s] can you fit in this room&amp;quot; &amp;ndash; Asked at &lt;a href="http://www.glassdoor.com/Interview/Google-Interview-RVW529787.htm"&gt;Google, People Analyst&lt;/a&gt; position&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
		&amp;quot;Out of 25 horses, pick the fastest 3 horses. In each race, only 5 horses can run at the same time. What is the minimum number of races required?&amp;quot; &amp;ndash; Asked at &lt;a href="http://www.glassdoor.com/Interview/Bloomberg-L-P-Interview-RVW400050.htm"&gt;Bloomberg LP Financial, Software Developer&lt;/a&gt; position&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
		&amp;quot;If you could be any superhero, who would it be?&amp;quot; &amp;ndash; Asked at &lt;a href="http://www.glassdoor.com/Interview/AT-and-T-Interview-RVW546645.htm"&gt;AT&amp;amp;T, Customer Sales Representative&lt;/a&gt; position&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
		&amp;quot;You have a birthday cake and have exactly 3 slices to cut it into 8 equal pieces. How do you do it?&amp;quot; &amp;ndash; Asked at &lt;a href="http://www.glassdoor.com/GD/Interview/BlackRock-Interview-Questions-E9331.htm?filter.jobTitleExact=Portfolio+Management+Group-Fixed+Income+Analyst"&gt;Blackrock Portfolio Management Group, Fixed Income Analyst&lt;/a&gt; position&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
		&amp;quot;Given the numbers 1 to 1000, what is the minimum numbers guesses needed to find a specific number if you are given the hint &amp;quot;higher&amp;quot; or &amp;quot;lower&amp;quot; for each guess you make?&amp;quot; &amp;ndash; Asked at &lt;a href="http://www.glassdoor.com/Interview/Facebook-Interview-RVW370781.htm"&gt;Facebook, Software Engineer&lt;/a&gt; position&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
		&amp;quot;If you had 5,623 participants in a tournament, how many games would need to be played to determine the winner?&amp;quot; &amp;ndash; Asked at &lt;a href="http://www.glassdoor.com/Interview/Amazon-com-Manager-Interview-Questions-EI_IE6036.0,10_KO11,18.htm"&gt;Amazon, Manager&lt;/a&gt; position&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
		&amp;quot;An apple costs &lt;span class="xn-money"&gt;20 cents&lt;/span&gt;, an orange costs &lt;span class="xn-money"&gt;40 cents&lt;/span&gt;, and a grapefruit costs &lt;span class="xn-money"&gt;60 cents&lt;/span&gt;, how much is a pear?&amp;quot; &amp;ndash; Asked at &lt;a href="http://www.glassdoor.com/Interview/Epic-Systems-Corporation-Interview-RVW415446.htm"&gt;Epic Systems, Project Manager&lt;/a&gt; position&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
		&amp;quot;There are three boxes, one contains only apples, one contains only oranges, and one contains both apples and oranges. The boxes have been incorrectly labeled such that no label identifies the actual contents of the box it labels. Opening just one box, and without looking in the box, you take out one piece of fruit. By looking at the fruit, how can you immediately label all of the boxes correctly?&amp;quot; &amp;ndash; Asked at &lt;a href="http://www.glassdoor.com/Interview/Apple-Interview-RVW674756.htm"&gt;Apple, Software QA Engineer&lt;/a&gt; position&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
		&amp;quot;How many traffic lights in &lt;span class="xn-location"&gt;Manhattan&lt;/span&gt;?&amp;quot; &amp;ndash; Asked at &lt;a href="http://www.glassdoor.com/Interview/Argus-Information-and-Advisory-Services-Interview-RVW407846.htm"&gt;Argus Information &amp;amp; Advisory Services, Analyst&lt;/a&gt; position&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
		&amp;quot;You are in a dark room with no light. You need matching socks for your interview and you have 19 grey socks and 25 black socks. What are the chances you will get a matching pair?&amp;quot; &amp;ndash; Asked at &lt;a href="http://www.glassdoor.com/Interview/Eze-Castle-Interview-RVW404325.htm"&gt;Eze Castle, Quality Assurance&lt;/a&gt; position&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
		&amp;quot;What do wood and alcohol have in common?&amp;quot; &amp;ndash; Asked at &lt;a href="http://www.glassdoor.com/Interview/Guardsmark-Interview-RVW391487.htm"&gt;Guardsmark, Staff Writer&lt;/a&gt; position&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
		&amp;quot;How do you weigh an elephant without using a weigh machine?&amp;quot; &amp;ndash; Asked at &lt;a href="http://www.glassdoor.com/Interview/IBM-Interview-RVW474381.htm"&gt;IBM, Software Engineer&lt;/a&gt; position&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
		&amp;quot;You have 8 pennies, 7 weigh the same, one weighs less. You also have a judges scale. Find the one that weighs less in less than 3 steps.&amp;quot; &amp;ndash; Asked at &lt;a href="http://www.glassdoor.com/Interview/Intel-Corporation-Interview-RVW488633.htm"&gt;Intel, Systems Validation Engineer&lt;/a&gt; position&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
		&amp;quot;Why do you think only a small percentage of the population makes over $150K?&amp;quot; &amp;ndash; Asked at &lt;a href="http://www.glassdoor.com/Interview/New-York-Life-Interview-RVW364498.htm"&gt;New York Life, Sales Agent&lt;/a&gt; position&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
		&amp;quot;You are in charge of 20 people, organize them to figure out how many bicycles were sold in your area last year.&amp;quot; &amp;ndash; Asked at &lt;a href="http://www.glassdoor.com/Interview/Schlumberger-Interview-RVW420783.htm"&gt;Schlumberger, Field Engineer&lt;/a&gt; position&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
		&amp;quot;How many bottles of beer are drank in the city over the week?&amp;quot; &amp;ndash; Asked at &lt;a href="http://www.glassdoor.com/Interview/The-Nielsen-Company-Interview-RVW560366.htm"&gt;The Nielsen Company, Research Analyst&lt;/a&gt; position&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
		&amp;quot;What&amp;#39;s the square root of 2000?&amp;quot; &amp;ndash; Asked at &lt;a href="http://www.glassdoor.com/Interview/UBS-Interview-RVW396678.htm"&gt;UBS, Sales and Trading&lt;/a&gt; position&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
		&amp;quot;A train leaves &lt;span class="xn-location"&gt;San Antonio&lt;/span&gt; for Huston at 60mph. Another train leaves Huston for &lt;span class="xn-location"&gt;San Antonio&lt;/span&gt; at 80mph. Huston and &lt;span class="xn-location"&gt;San Antonio&lt;/span&gt; are 300 miles apart. If a bird leaves &lt;span class="xn-location"&gt;San Antonio&lt;/span&gt; at 100mph, and turns around and flies back once it reaches the Huston train, and continues to fly between the two, how far will it have flown when they collide?&amp;quot;- Asked at &lt;a href="http://www.glassdoor.com/Interview/USAA-Interview-RVW483976.htm"&gt;USAA, Software Engineer&lt;/a&gt; position&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
		&amp;quot;How are M&amp;amp;M&amp;#39;s made?&amp;quot; &amp;ndash; Asked at &lt;a href="http://www.glassdoor.com/Interview/U-S-Bank-Interview-RVW456652.htm"&gt;US Bank, Leadership Program Development&lt;/a&gt; position&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
		&amp;quot;What would you do if you just inherited a pizzeria from your uncle?&amp;quot; &amp;ndash; Asked at &lt;a href="http://www.glassdoor.com/Interview/Volkswagen-Interview-RVW410669.htm"&gt;Volkswagen, Business Analyst&lt;/a&gt; position&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	The interview questions are part of the Glassdoor &lt;a href="http://www.glassdoor.com/Interview/index.htm"&gt;Interview Reviews&lt;/a&gt; section, offering in-depth accounts of the interview process for specific job titles at specific companies &amp;ndash; all for free. To date, approximately 80,000 interview questions around the world have been collected. Interview Reviews include details from actual candidates about the entire hiring process -- from the interview format and average duration to overall difficulty. Each review also includes details as to whether an offer was made and whether it was accepted or rejected -- and why -- along with any negotiation tips.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/noria/reliableplant/tags/talent_management/~4/1wv9aI2E-vg" height="1" width="1" alt=""/&gt;</description>
