            <title>Chart: Real earnings changes by month since November 2009</title>
            <description>&lt;p&gt;
	Real average hourly earnings for all employees fell 0.1 percent from October to November, seasonally adjusted. This decrease stems from a 0.1-percent increase in the Consumer Price Index for All Urban Consumers (CPI-U), while average hourly earnings remained unchanged.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="center"&gt;
	&lt;img alt="Over-the-month percent change in real average hourly earnings for all employees, seasonally adjusted, November 2009November 2010" border="1" height="360" src="http://www.bls.gov/opub/ted/images/2010/ted_20101220.png" width="580" /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
